@startuml cabin_air_temp_to_datc_defog_vent_mode_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Cabin Air Temp To DATC Defog Vent Mode Signal Flow\n(cabin-air temperature -> DATC local HVAC defog and vent-mode decision)

participant "Cabin-air sensor bus" as Cabin #F4F7FB
participant "TMU service bus" as TMU #E8F0FE
participant "DATC\nHVAC owner" as DATC #E8F7E8
participant "HVAC state/actuator bus" as HvacBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\ncomfort readers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== DATC Inputs ==

Cabin -> DATC : frmCabinAirStateMsg\nCabinTemp
TMU -> DATC : frmTmuServiceStateMsg\nRemoteClimateReq / TmuLinkState /\nTmuServiceMode / SignalBars
activate DATC
DATC -> DATC : cabinAirInputStale =\nethIsRecentTick(gCabinAirRxMs, 300)
DATC -> DATC : tmuInputStale =\nethIsRecentTick(gTmuServiceRxMs, 300)
DATC -> DATC : if cabin-air stale then\nCabinTemp = 24
DATC -> DATC : if TMU remote climate active and link healthy\nthen remote profile wins
DATC -> DATC : else derive local HVAC posture from CabinTemp
DATC -> DATC : cold cabin -> DefogMode=1,\nVentMode=1, warmer set temp
DATC -> DATC : hot cabin -> AC on,\nVentMode=2, higher blower
note right of DATC
Representative gating inputs
- CabinTemp
- RemoteClimateReq
- TmuLinkState
- TmuServiceMode
- SignalBars
end note

== DATC Publish ==

DATC -> HvacBus : frmHvacStateMsg\nCabinSetTemp / BlowerLevel / AcCompressorOn
DATC -> HvacBus : frmHvacActuatorMsg\nVentMode / DefogMode / FanRpmStep
note right of DATC
Representative outputs
- CabinSetTemp
- BlowerLevel
- VentMode
- DefogMode
- FanRpmStep
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

HvacBus -> Obs : HVAC actuator visibility /\ncomfort observers
deactivate DATC

note over Cabin, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Cabin-air temperature and TMU service context reach DATC
2. DATC checks source freshness and remote-climate gating
3. DATC derives local defog / vent / blower posture
4. DATC publishes HVAC state and actuator outputs
end note

@enduml
